      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KID (3) took advantage of a low draw last start with an all-the-way win (22.62) at this track in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 over 390m. Form from his last run is proving strong. The hardest to beat again. SMILING LILY (4) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a 4.5 lengths second over 400m Geelong in 22.92. Will give a great sight again. HARTLAND BUDDY (6) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at Warrnambool in a handy 22.37 beating Dimora Stripey. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. ASCEND IGLOO (1) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
